<div><h3>PSCI 170 - American Political Thought and Behavior </h3>  <hr>Type of Course: Lecture, Discussion<br>
This course explores factors that shape Americans&#8217; political values, beliefs, attitudes, and expectations of government. It explores how our partisan orientations are formed and how they relate to contemporary conceptions of liberalism and conservativism in America.Â  We will devote particular attention to how partisanship and ideology change and how attitudes about race and gender relate to partisanship and ideology.<br>
